  "title": "Riding a Bike",
  "story": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "ce77a80b8686100b",
      "text": "Importantly, cocreating forward is anchored in objects of a specific kind. First, the object anchoring the process is a “tool.” Tools privilege action over all else. In cocreating forward, the tool imbricates the knowledge of all parties involved in the cocreation process such that the concepts, labels, and ideas represent the insights brought forth by researchers, managers, and others involved in the cocreation process. However, such knowledge is fully available in “knowing” and not only in reified concepts in the tool; in other words, “knowing is the epistemic work that is done as part of action or practice, like that of riding a bike” (Cook & Brown, 1999: 387) [⇒[[Generative Dance]]]. One can read about riding a bike, but it is in the act of riding that the knowledge is deployed and further experiential understanding is gained. In the same way, cocreating forward involves anchoring the process in a tool that represents various inputs (or knowledge of different parties) and at the same time allows for imagining potential uses (or knowing). Use is in the future, and hence by focusing on action and imagining use, researchers and managers can move beyond the concerns of the present."
